OL,3,CNoel Clarke loses libel case against
OL,4,CThe Guardian publisher
OL,6,FPhilip Williams, representing the
OL,7,Factor, said that his client was a
OL,8,F"casualty" of a media "purge"
OL,9,Ffollowing the emergence of the MeToo
OL,10,Fmovement.
OL,12,FHowever, Gavin Millar KC, for GNM,
OL,13,Fsaid there was "not a shred of
OL,14,Fevidence" to support Clarke's claim of
OL,15,Fa conspiracy, describing it as
OL,16,F"nonsensical and rather desperate
OL,17,Fspeculation".
OL,19,FMrs Justice Steyn agreed and said the
OL,20,Fconspiracy claim did not have a
OL,21,F"proper foundation".
