OL,3,CNoel Clarke loses libel case against
OL,4,CThe Guardian publisher
OL,6,F"It lacked any proper foundation and
OL,7,Fled to numerous witnesses being asked
OL,8,Fspeculative questions as to their
OL,9,Fconnections, without a case being put
OL,10,Fthat they conspired and colluded to
OL,11,Finvent allegations, or any evidential
OL,12,Fbasis on which such a case could have
OL,13,Fbeen put."
OL,15,FGuardian editor-in-chief Katharine
OL,16,FViner welcomed the judge's ruling and
OL,17,Fsaid its libel victory over Clarke was
OL,18,Fa landmark for investigative
OL,19,Fjournalism in the UK.
