OL,3,CNoel Clarke loses libel case against
OL,4,CThe Guardian publisher
OL,6,FIn a statement, she said: "The judge
OL,7,Fruled, in extremely clear language,
OL,8,Fthat the Guardian's reporting was
OL,9,Fsubstantially true, and our belief
OL,10,Fthat the reporting was in the public
OL,11,Finterest was undoubtedly reasonable.
OL,13,F"This judgment is a deserved victory
OL,14,Ffor those women who suffered because
OL,15,Fof the behaviour of Noel Clarke.
OL,17,F"Going to court is difficult and
OL,18,Fstressful, yet more than 20 women
OL,19,Fagreed to testify in the High Court,
OL,20,Frefusing to be bullied or intimidated.
